"['Most payments companies have figured out the loophole that you have bank accounts in both countries and then you can facilitate instant payment to the customer by floating it through your own balance sheet.', 'Not captured in slide 2 is CLS Bank International. Between Tokyo and the US, the funds flow through payment submissions to CLS and possibly again between US and Mexico, depending on the size of the banks involved. \n\nGreat post.', 'You can find all FinTech companies focused on the Payments here:\n\nhttps://www.awesomefintech.com/category/payments/\n\nOriginal research by Jackson Bubala can be found here:\n\nhttps://stealingsigns.substack.com/p/an-intro-to-b2b-cross-border-payments', 'Great post!', 'True. But not every company is ready to go global, nor pay for the overhead. But if you do things right, yes, that’s what you’ll eventually do.', 'Thank you!', 'I meant the payments providers, not the people trying to send money.', 'Sure. Same way TransferWise started.']"
